The BMI value of at least 25 indicates that one person is overweight and persons with BMI over 30 are considered obese.
You can calculate the BMI by accessing: 1.usa.gov/1D0ZqDv.
For the new study, researchers from the General Min-Sheng Hospital in Taiwan used data gathered after 2007 in a trial comparing two types of bariatric surgery - bypass gastric and gastrectomy in the manson - in the medical treatment of type 2 diabetes to people with mild obesity.
Mean BMI in patients who have undergone surgery decreased from 31 to 24.5 to the end of the fifth year of the study.
In the meantime, BMI in people who received neurgic treatments against diabetes remained at almost the same level, namely 29.
