The government approved, on Wednesday, "The National Strategy on Immigration for the period 2015-2018" and "The Action Plan for the current year", documents considered to be "a stage that Romania is still going through in efforts to modernise the immigration management process on the national territory", according to a press release.
The source mentioned shows that the strategy aims to effectively manage the phenomenon of immigration, including general strategic objectives, specific objectives and action guidelines that reflect policies set at European level, adapted to national realities.
In view of the problems faced by the countries of the immediate vicinity of Romania, measures are taken to manage the situation of unity and coherence as a result of the possible influx of illegal immigrants into the territory of Romania, generated by the political, social, economic or military crisis.
"Roman authorities will contribute to the creation of a flexible admission system, but at the same time, they will give special attention to citizens from states with potential migrationists or who can harm national security," adds the remembered source.
The strategy identifies a number of factors that can influence immigration and asylum, including maintaining the conflict in Syria, reactivating the conflict in Iraq, maintaining an unstable situation in the border areas of Romania (Ukraine, Transnistria), perpetuating and increasing the intensity of the Israeli-Palestinian armed conflict.
On the other hand, the document also sets out a few general strategic objectives related to immigration, such as: promoting legal migration, more rigorous controls of the legality of the seat of third-country nationals on the territory of Romania and the appropriate application of removal measures and restrictive measures, improving the national asylum system.
The national strategy also includes specific objectives relevant to the implementation and implementation of the overall strategic objectives.
Among these are: facilitating access to Romania's territory of third-party citizens who respond to the demands for the occupation of the labour force, promoting the access of third-country nationals to Romanian higher education institutions for areas and professions identified as deficit.
With reference to the 2015 Action Plan, the Government appreciates that it represents "a means of establishing concrete activities leading to the creation of a flexible system for halting the growing migration phenomenon".
